"{\"uid\": \"cyclingnews.com-news-laura-kenny-retires-from-cycling-ahead-of-paris-2024-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  'I have had an absolute blast but now is the time for me to hang that bike up'  When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now subscribed  Your newsletter sign-up was successful  Laura Kennyhas announced her retirement from cycling with immediate effect, bringing the curtain down on a career that saw her win five Olympic gold medals and seven world titles.\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 532, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 353, \"end\": 358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9947626938894374, \"rank\": 0.005264867181767019, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Briton hadbeen preparing to participate in her fourth Olympic Games this summer, though British Cyclingperformancedirector Stephen Park indicated earlier this month that she had only a \\\"slim chance\\\" of lining up in Paris.\", \"from\": 534, \"to\": 759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 534, \"end\": 544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Briton\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Briton\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q25379\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Briton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Briton\"}, {\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9964494360267538, \"rank\": 0.002571487894484973, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 661, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Park\", \"score\": 0.9526188091527281, \"rank\": 0.041883618186645405, \"text\": \"Stephen Park\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Park\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Park\"}, {\"begin\": 753, \"end\": 758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999991960067, \"rank\": 8.040033637707361e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Monday, Kenny confirmed her retirement from cycling.\", \"from\": 760, \"to\": 815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I always knew deep down I would know when the right time was.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 879, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have had an absolute blast but now is the time for me to hang that bike up,\\\" Kennytold the BBC.\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenny was one of the stars of the London 2012 Olympics, winning gold in both the omnium and team pursuit.\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 1084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.524880837134716e-17, \"text\": \"London 2012 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She repeated the feat in Rio four years later and then added gold in the Madison and a silver in the team pursuit in Tokyo in 2021.\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1110, \"end\": 1113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999988105753598, \"rank\": 1.1894260694844086e-06, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Madison_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9977020374405522, \"rank\": 0.0023032553539838953, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Madison_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Madison_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9741109609111919, \"rank\": 0.02657706966087191, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I never thought I would go to a home Games, let alone go on to win two gold medals,\\\" Kenny said of the London Olympics.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1322, \"end\": 1337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7272528903982137e-13, \"text\": \"London Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I look back, I am like 'wow, those two weeks did really change my life.'\\\"\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although Kenny competed on the road, including with the Wiggle-Honda squad in 2013 and 2014, track cycling always remained her priority, and she collected rainbow jerseys in the omnium, scratch and team pursuit, as well as fourteen European titles in the velodrome.\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1476, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wiggle_High5_Pro_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wiggle-Honda\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wiggle_High5_Pro_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wiggle_High5_Pro_Cycling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her husband Jason Kenny, himself a seven-time Olympic champion, retired from cycling at the start of 2022.\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1699, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jason Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The couple have two children, born in 2017 and 2023.\", \"from\": 1794, \"to\": 1846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 1848, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's been in my head a little while, the sacrifices of leaving the children and your family at home are really quite big and it really is a big decision to make,\\\" Kenny said on Monday.\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 2137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"More and more, I was struggling to do that.\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More people asking me what races was I doing, what training camps was I going on - I did not want to go ultimately and that's what it came down to.\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew the minute I was getting those feelings.\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Once I said to Jase, 'I do not think I want to ride a bike anymore', I started to feel relief.\\\"\", \"from\": 2382, \"to\": 2477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a statement released by British Cycling, performance director Stephen Park paid tribute to Kenny's impact on the sport.\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2506, \"end\": 2521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}, {\"begin\": 2544, \"end\": 2556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Park\", \"score\": 0.9526188091527281, \"rank\": 0.041883618186645405, \"text\": \"Stephen Park\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Park\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Park\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Laura hangs up her wheels as not just one of the sport's greatest riders, but as one of the greatest sporting talents our country has ever produced,\\\" Park said.\", \"from\": 2603, \"to\": 2764, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2604, \"end\": 2609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9947626938894374, \"rank\": 0.005264867181767019, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She has been a beacon of inspiration for so many, young and old, and I am sure that the entire British cycling community will join me in wishing her the very best in the next chapter of her life.\\\"\", \"from\": 2765, \"to\": 2962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2861, \"end\": 2876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barry Ryan was Head of Features at Cyclingnews until 2024.\", \"from\": 2964, \"to\": 3022, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2964, \"end\": 2969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"score\": 0.9988005867120635, \"rank\": 0.0012008535702623029, \"text\": \"Barry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\"}, {\"begin\": 2970, \"end\": 2974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.9999733961663917, \"rank\": 2.6589118394737975e-05, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is currently Editor-in-chief at Domestique.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3058, \"end\": 3068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domestique\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Domestique\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domestique\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domestique\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has covered professional cycling since 2010, reporting from the Tour de France, Giro d'Italia and events from Argentina to Japan.\", \"from\": 3070, \"to\": 3202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3137, \"end\": 3151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999998567546, \"rank\": 1.0996132039532298e-10, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 3153, \"end\": 3166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"score\": 0.996852359047248, \"rank\": 0.0022119854881003267, \"text\": \"Giro d'Italia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\"}, {\"begin\": 3183, \"end\": 319